\item \strong{Is the basis dimension \code{k} large enough?} \code{k_check} is
\code{\link[mgcv:k.check]{mgcv::k.check()}}'s table (k', edf, k-index, p-value) with the term
names mapped back to the user's columns. A \code{k_flag} column marks the
spline smooths where a low k-index together with a small p-value
suggests \code{k} is too low and the model should be refitted with a
larger \code{k}. Random-effect terms (by-speaker / by-item) are flagged
\code{"na"} because the k-index is not a meaningful check for them.
\item \strong{Is there leftover temporal autocorrelation?} \code{acf} is the lag /
autocorrelation of the residuals with the white-noise band in
\code{acf_ci}. Autocorrelation decaying slowly across lags is the signal
